-- South African Companies to Get Illegal Cash Amnesty, Business Day Reports
-- Antony Sguazzin
-- 2010-07-02T04:52:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/south-african-companies-to-get-illegal-cash-amnesty-business-day-reports.html

          
          
             South African companies will benefit 
from an amnesty for taking money out of the country illegally 
if they disclose it and pay a penalty equivalent to 10 percent 
of the value of the asset, Johannesburg’s Business Day 
newspaper reported, citing the country’s central bank.  
          
          


  


        